/.claude/worktrees
.env
scripts/jira/dist/
# where-are-we ledger L2 (HIMMEL-516): regenerated-from-live-sources cache, not
# source of truth — never commit it.
/.where-are-we/
# node_modules anywhere — none are tracked. A per-package list let
# marketplace/plugins/*/node_modules/ slip through and be sweepable (HIMMEL-371).
node_modules/
/.claude/settings.local.json
# tokensave MCP code-graph state (local SQLite DB, session-generated — never commit).
/.tokensave/
# graphify knowledge-graph artifacts (HIMMEL-621). The DERIVED GRAPH is tracked
# (HIMMEL-1123) — extraction is LLM-backed and genuinely expensive, so stations
# that cannot afford to build it (win2: "no resources") pull it instead of
# re-extracting. That is the cost-of-regeneration split: tokensave regenerates
# free on local CPU and stays ignored above; a graph does not.
# WSL needs no transport (HIMMEL-996 shares the Windows store over /mnt/c) —
# this is for physically separate hosts.
#
# Ignore the CONTENTS, then re-include only the two portable artifacts. The
# per-machine STAMPS stay local on purpose:
#   .graphify_root  - an ABSOLUTE corpus path; committed, it makes the freshness
#                     guard resolve win1's path on win2 and fail closed as
#                     "corpus orphaned" (HIMMEL-1116 makes it portable).
#   manifest.json   - mtimes are machine-local, and after a checkout every file
#                     is checkout-fresh, so a pulled graph would read as FRESH
#                     regardless of its real age.
#   cache/          - graphify's semantic cache; local, and large.
graphify-out/*
!graphify-out/graph.json
!graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
/.claude/skills/graphify/
# Generated/junk artifacts that must never be committed (HIMMEL-371).
# NOT package-lock.json globally — 6 legit npm packages track theirs. The
# wrong-PM lockfile case (a package-lock.json inside a bun package, left by the
# npm-audit pre-push gates) is prevented per-bun-package via that package's own
# .gitignore (e.g. marketplace/plugins/luna-correlate/, scripts/luna-vitals/),
# and still backstopped by the check-artifact-leakage pre-commit hook.
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
# end-session-wiki hook local artifacts — contain raw transcript excerpts (potential secrets).
# Match any .claude/ dir (the hook writes into the cwd's .claude/, e.g. scripts/telegram/.claude/).
**/.claude/end-session-wiki.log
**/.claude/end-session-wiki.log.old
# Handover transient state
.last-consolidate.json
**/handovers/*/.last-consolidate.json
.pending-new-item*
**/handovers/*/.pending-new-item*
.pending-consolidate*
**/handovers/*/.pending-consolidate*
# auto-arm-on-cap / auto-arm-on-subagent-cap runtime snapshots (HIMMEL-276) —
# the hooks write these into himmel handovers/ as untracked clutter on main.
# (Followup: redirect the hook write path to HANDOVER_DIR — see HIMMEL ticket.)
handovers/auto-arm-status-*.md
# arm-resume lock files (arms.jsonl) — transient arming-lock state that lands in
# the himmel handovers/ stub as untracked clutter; observed staged on main
# (HIMMEL-1024), same class as the auto-arm-status snapshots above.
handovers/.locks/
# Overnight-mode reports/recovery artifacts — auto-generated session state
# (morning-report.sh et al.) that belongs in the state repo, not the himmel
# handovers/ stub. Archived copies live in <state-repo> handovers/yotamleo/himmel/.
handovers/overnight-report-*.md
handovers/overnight-recovery-*.md
# Cross-project handover content moved to <state-repo> in HIMMEL-13 —
# prevent accidental re-tracking if the operator's local copy still
# exists or gets re-created here by an out-of-date tool.
/handovers/luna/
/handovers/manual_notes.md
/handovers/random_dreams.md
# Runtime artifacts that pollute primary-worktree git status
.claire/
/.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
/.playwright-mcp
# /improve disk artifacts — Mode A inline path. Mode B writes under HANDOVER_DIR.
/.improve/
# /gemini-bg background-run output sink (HIMMEL-158)
logs/gemini/
# superpowers design docs were removed for OSS (HIMMEL-297); overnight-mode
# Mode A (no HANDOVER_DIR) regenerates plans under docs/superpowers/plans/ —
# keep those local, never re-track the folder into the public repo.
/docs/superpowers/
# Codex artifacts (HIMMEL-427: codex IS now wired). The guardrail wiring is
# TRACKED (hooks.json + the run-hook.cmd polyglot + its README); codex's local
# runtime config, sessions, and auto-generated slash-command→skill mirrors stay
# ignored. (AGENTS.md itself is tracked separately.)
.codex/*
!.codex/hooks.json
!.codex/run-hook.cmd
!.codex/codex-hook-adapter.sh
!.codex/README.md
.agents/skills/source-command-*/
# himmel-contributor marker (opt-in; enables doc-guard gate) — never commit it
.himmel-dev
# per-operator CR registry overlay (account quota state) — never commit (HIMMEL-727)
scripts/cr/critics.local.json
# per-machine lane availability/override overlay (himmelctl config) — never commit (HIMMEL-758)
scripts/lanes/lanes.local.json
# machine-local grok tool-schema cache dir — never commit (HIMMEL-876)
/mcps/
